<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99687252920735></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99687252920735><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/item.html?item=4362&mid=99687252920735>important classes</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=62931><span id= >Manorien</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 3rd 5:02 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>im not sure how many realize this: every class is important. any class should have a chance on this belt if they have worked hard for their guild and shown dedication to the guild. An item like this is given on merit and not just to the "necessary classes."  furthermore, there are only three classes that a raid cannot succeed without: warriors, clerics, and rogues. when fighting in places like ToV, sleepers, and bosses of velious, mezzing isnt even considered.  a designated warrior will tank the add and there is only ONE tank tanking the whole battle with 3 or 4 clerics casting CH.  that is why the clerics are necessary.  and no raid cannot succeed without enough rogues, as they can do more dmg than ANY other class especially on long battles like one involving tormax.  however, this belt should go to any character that has merited this belt by dedication and hard work.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
